issue.title: View component helpers not available
issue.body:
### Describe the bug

I ran into an issue with a helper in a view component I'm trying to render in LookBook.

Inside a VC I'm using this format [`helpers.svg`](https://github.com/avo-hq/avo/pull/3632/files#diff-76d4c03eb15d4344cb7307670c8bdb29db18497047c139db9fc29882971d30eaR72) to call an [`svg`](https://github.com/avo-hq/avo/blob/main/app/helpers/avo/application_helper.rb#L63) method I have in a Rails helper module.

I'm getting this error which is probably because you're running it in an isolated context somewhere.

> undefined method `svg' for an instance of #<Class:0x000000012595be08>

We use the `helpers.` pattern everywhere and before we go and refactor everything, maybe there's something that can fix it for us.

I made a screen recording of the issue where I go a bit more in depth.

Thanks a lot!

https://www.loom.com/share/24234a1c06fe47f583fa5302a8754f00?sid=644d3ee4-13b3-417b-b1c9-15c06aedca8b

### Screenshots

If applicable, add screenshots to help explain your problem.

### Version numbers 

Please complete the following information:

* Lookbook: 2.3.8
* ViewComponent: 3.12
* Rails: 8.0.1
* Ruby: 3.3.1

release.name: LibreAuth 0.13.0
release.body:
### Added
- Optional additional HMAC with an external salt before or after hashing the password.
- The C-bindings documentation has been improved.

### Changed
- The output base for HOTP and TOTP must now be valid UTF-8.
- `LIBREAUTH_OATH_CODE_INVALID_UTF8` has been renamed `LIBREAUTH_OATH_INVALID_UTF8`.
- The `output_base_len` parameter in the `libreauth_hotp_cfg` and `libreauth_totp_cfg` structures has been dropped.
- The PBKDF2 `hash` parameter has been renamed `hmac`.
- The HashFunction has been moved to a dedicated module and its C-bindings renamed accordingly.

### Fixed
- The project now compiles on Microsoft Windows.

* Consolidate docs: drop _internal/_sources; move architecture

- Clarify how to start/stop and access the local docs server

* Simplify nav; exclude architecture/components/_sources from build

- Add exclude plugin to ignore architecture/components/_sources/*

Capturing my changes thus far while I go off to educate myself about rST/Sphinx refs vs
links. As such, this duplicates a reference link in a way I don't like:

    :ref:`Automating Downloads <guides/getting_started/automating_downloads:docker and

If you want to fix that or are OK with the duplication, this should be ready to
go. Otherwise, I'll fix and force push once I've learned how to do this correctly.

blocks and the separate CPU/GPU passthrough code blocks because I find comments in
example code to be more clear, more readable, and more approachable. This also has the
benefit of putting informative comments in the resulting user's configuration. For
example, imagine a user that learns only later that they require GPU passthrough, their
configuration is already ready to get them started. This comes at the cost some repeated
comments (`environment:` and `deploy:` for GPU passthrough) and the fancy Sphinx
highlighting of relevant lines. I think the trade-off is a net benefit for users.

issue.title: Reuse same TCP connection for downloads
issue.body:
TCP connection speeds tend to take a while to ramp up. Making separate connections for two downloads may be fine for slower connections where it doesn't make a difference, but on fast connections a lot of time is wasted on waiting the speed to ramp up.
Reusing a connection (or multiple connections, see #58) would make this problem go away as it would only ramp up once for all downloads.
